	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The fan failed on my previous video card, causing lockups and stuff, and it wasn't immediately obvious why.  It wasn't particularly loud, and was in a hard to see spot, so I only noticed it by touching it.  CPU fans often have alarms, at least.  I replaced the fan and it worked for a while, after a year or two though I just replaced the whole thing when problems recurred.  If your CPU is just slowing down, hopefully it's safe from damage.<br /><br />Using a program to monitor temperature and fan speeds is nice, but I've noticed isn't very enlightening if you don't know what the normal values should be.  But I'd say to try that out, then blow out the heatsink with compressed air (do it outside, of course), and then re-check and you'll almost definitely see a lower temperature.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


